solid-pod-rs
============

This crate is a Rust implementation of a Solid Pod server providing
WAC (Web Access Control), LDP (Linked Data Platform) resource/container
semantics, NIP-98 HTTP authentication, and Solid Notifications.

Attribution
-----------

The initial WAC evaluator, LDP container logic, NIP-98 auth module,
and pod provisioning flows were extracted from the `pod-worker` crate
in the community-forum-rs project:

    https://github.com/DreamLab-AI/dreamlab-ai-website
    Path: community-forum-rs/crates/pod-worker

The community-forum-rs pod-worker was itself authored by the DreamLab AI
team as a Rust port of the original TypeScript `workers/pod-api/`.

The project architecture and feature model draw heavily on
JavaScriptSolidServer ("JSS"), maintained by the
JavaScriptSolidServer contributors:

    https://github.com/JavaScriptSolidServer/JavaScriptSolidServer

JSS is licensed AGPL-3.0-only. It is vendored read-only under
`references/javascript-solid-server/` for API parity reference during
Rust porting. It is not built, executed, or linked into this crate.

